 lower than the aforementioned predicted value, and\n39 + or - 4 and 31 + or - 6 for the values of northern- and\nsouthern-hemispheres' sunspot numbers at the maximum epoch of Solar Cycle 25.\nOverall, our results suggest that the amplitude of Solar Cycle 25 would be\n25%-40% smaller, and the corresponding north-south asymmetry would be much\nsmaller, than those of Solar Cycle 24.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Jan 2021 14:31:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-26"}
